  "prompt": "What is a cake mix?",
  "response": "A cake mix is a pre-packaged blend of dry ingredients used to bake a cake. Typically, it includes flour, sugar, baking powder, and sometimes other ingredients like flavorings or dried egg. To use a cake mix, you usually just need to add water, oil, and sometimes eggs, then mix and bake according to the package instructions. Cake mixes are popular because they save time and ensure consistent results, making baking easier for people of all skill levels.",
